usage: wator.py [-h] [-c CHRONONS] [-f FISHES] [--fishspawn FISHSPAWN]
                [-s SHARKS] [--sharkspawn SHARKSPAWN]
                [--sharkstarve SHARKSTARVE] [-S] [-t] [-x X] [-y Y]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -c CHRONONS, --chronons CHRONONS
                        maximum number of chronons to calculate, default
                        999999
  -f FISHES, --fishes FISHES
                        initial number of fishes
  --fishspawn FISHSPAWN
                        age that a fish spawns at, default 2, must be greater
                        than 0
  -s SHARKS, --sharks SHARKS
                        initial number of sharks
  --sharkspawn SHARKSPAWN
                        age that a sharks spawns at, default 5, must be
                        greater than 0
  --sharkstarve SHARKSTARVE
                        chronons that a shark can live without eating, default
                        3, must be greater than 0
  -S, --System          use SystemRandom giving unique runs, otherwise,
                        default to a seed of 42
  -t, --traditional     traditional search pattern
  -x X                  number of horizontal cells, default 200
  -y Y                  number of vertical cells, default 200
